  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3349",
  "title": "HierarchicalMenu click on the parent element behaviour",
  "body": "**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe 🙏**\r\n\r\nWith the current implementation of the `hierarchicalMenu` a click on the parent level removes the current level but also the parent. But actually it's maybe not the expected behaviour. You can take a look at [this example](https://v3--instantsearchjs.netlify.com/stories/?selectedStory=HierarchicalMenu.default):\r\n\r\n- click on  \"Audio > Docks, Radios & Boomboxes > Radios\"\r\n- click on \"Audio > Docks, Radios & Boomboxes\"\r\n\r\nWe could expect to be at the level \"Docks, Radios & Boomboxes\" (this is how [Amazon](https://www.amazon.com/s//www.amazon.com/s/ref=sr_nr_n_1?fst=as%3Aoff&rh=n%3A2335752011%2Cn%3A2407749011%2Ck%3Aiphone&keywords=iphone&ie=UTF8&qid=1544795775&rnid=2335753011&ajr=0&ajr=0) works) but we are at the \"Audio\" level.\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like 🤔**\r\n\r\nRather than removing the current and parent level we could let the parent level refined.\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/issues/2016#issuecomment-447324757\r\n",
